	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Looks correct. The only thing that's not entirely accurate is when you say that the first byte of the name table selects the tile that will show up at the top left corner of the screen while the last byte selects the one that will show up at the bottom right corner. That is true only if the scroll is set to (0, 0), perfectly aligned to the name table. When games scroll, the apparent positions of those tiles will change.
<br />
<br />I hope I haven't confused you with this. You can ignore my comments until you look into scrolling though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

